Anonymous Thu 16 Mar 2023 13:26:19 No.55099620 Report
Quoted By:
If Spare in the Trunk really is finished now - and for the record I hope there's still more coming - I have to say I really liked it. I appreciated Allison's dynamic with Jack, like she's just trying to look out for him without asking anything in return. Both the main characters struggle really well with their shortcomings in a way that makes me feel bad for them, but hopeful that they'll be able to make it. It's good emotional writing, you did quite well at making them seem like real people in a real harsh world

I dunno if you're after feedback, but there's one thing I'd criticize significiantly even if it seems small. Right after Jack got hurt, Allison was very underdescribed. The bits after that were OK, but just that one part with those few paragraphs really confused me and made it hard to discern Allison's emotions or motivations, it seemed like she started to warm up to Lys far too quick considering how harsh her views were. I understand it's third person limited, but I think if you'd had a bit more focus what Jack perceives of Allison's thoughts instead of just describing her actions, it would have gone a long way to making her seem just conflicted and emotional instead of like she changed her mind about Lys three times in a row.

Just as a quick rough example, instead of
>She laughed and nodded. “Yeah. God, I don’t know about this.” Al wrapped her arms about herself. “Lys, you’re not an animal.”
Something like
>“Yeah. God, I don’t know about this,” Al gave a nervous laugh and a nod as she wrapped her arms about herself. She had an uncertain expression caught somewhere between guilt, sympathy and confusion, like she couldn't actually figure out what she should be feeling. "Look, Lys, you're not an animal..."
Obviously taking some liberties with it that you might not have intended, but you get what I mean I hope
